---
// src/pages/projects/selling-points-analytics.astro

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const pipeline = ['Source Data', 'SQL Query', 'Analytics DE', 'Selling Points', 'Reporting'];
---

<Layout title="Selling Points Analytics DE — SFMC" description="Building a Salesforce Marketing Cloud Data Extension that consolidates selling-point analytics into a reportable dataset.">
    <style>
        :root { --accent: #0055ff; --ink: #1a1a1a; --muted: #666; --line: #e1e4e6; }
        * { box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 20px 64px; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.6; }
        .back { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem; }
        .back:hover { color: var(--accent); }
        h1 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.6rem); margin: 16px 0 8px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
        .lede { font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 32px; max-width: 62ch; }
        .pipeline-label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 12px; }
        .pipeline { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 44px; }
        .step { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; color: #444; background: #f6f8fa; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; padding: 6px 12px; white-space: nowrap; }
        .arrow { color: #bbb; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 40px 0 14px; padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent); }
        h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin: 24px 0 6px; color: var(--accent); }
        p { margin: 0 0 16px; }
        ol.steps { margin: 0 0 16px; padding-left: 20px; }
        ol.steps li { margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .figure { margin: 24px 0 0; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; background: #fafbfc; }
        .figure img { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
        .figure figcaption { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); padding: 12px 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
        .img-placeholder { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-height: 300px; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; text-align: center; padding: 40px; }
    </style>

    <a href="/" class="back">← All projects</a>
    <h1>Selling Points Analytics Data Extension</h1>
    <p class="lede">
        Building a Salesforce Marketing Cloud Data Extension that consolidates selling-point analytics —
        turning raw source data into a structured, reportable dataset, surfaced on a landing page.
    </p>

    <p class="pipeline-label">Pipeline visual flow</p>
    <div class="pipeline">
        {pipeline.map((step, i) => (
            <div style="display: contents;">
                <span class="step">{step}</span>
                {i < pipeline.length - 1 && <span class="arrow">→</span>}
            </div>
        ))}
    </div>

    <h2>Background &amp; goal</h2>
    <p>
        Marketing teams need to know which selling points actually drive engagement and conversion — but that
        information usually sits scattered across raw send, engagement, and product data. The goal of this project
        is to consolidate it into a single, purpose-built Data Extension that surfaces performance <em>by selling
        point</em>, so the results can be read and reported on directly without manual assembly each time.
    </p>
    <p>
        The output is designed to feed a landing page that presents the analytics in a clean, shareable view for
        business stakeholders.
    </p>

    <h2>The process — building the Data Extension</h2>
    <p>
        The Data Extension is built as a repeatable pipeline, moving from raw source data through to a structured,
        reportable output:
    </p>
    <ol class="steps">
        <li><strong>Extract the source data.</strong> Pull the relevant records with SQL, filtered to the sends and selling points in scope.</li>
        <li><strong>Shape the Data Extension.</strong> Define explicit field types, lengths, and a primary key so each row maps cleanly to a selling point and its associated metrics.</li>
        <li><strong>Aggregate by selling point.</strong> Structure the query so metrics roll up per selling point, producing one clear record per point.</li>
        <li><strong>Refresh on schedule.</strong> Automate the pipeline so the Data Extension stays current as new data arrives.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Surfacing it on a landing page</h3>
    <p>
        The finished Data Extension feeds a landing page that reads directly from it, presenting selling-point
        performance in a readable, stakeholder-friendly layout — turning a back-end dataset into a shareable report.
    </p>

    <h2>The result</h2>
    <p>
        The screenshot below shows the analytics landing page produced from the Data Extension.
    </p>
<figure class="figure">
        <img src="/images/selling-points-analytics.png" alt="Selling points analytics landing page" />
        <figcaption>The analytics landing page generated from the selling-points Data Extension.</figcaption>
    </figure>
</Layout>